# Blueprint storage
#
# This folder holds blueprint JSON files written by the GitHub-backed storage
# layer at /lib/github-storage.ts. Each blueprint is stored as a single JSON
# file at /blueprints/{id}.json, where {id} is a 12-char nanoid.
#
# This .gitkeep is needed so the folder exists in the GitHub repo before any
# blueprints are created. Once the first blueprint is saved, this file can be
# removed or left alone.
